                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14478111" author="paulk" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2008 18:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Graeme, I couldn&apos;t think of a universal solution for non-nested properties so have implemented a poor man&apos;s solution. It will handle the case above (which I regard as an edge case) but probably then fails if you attempted to merge etc. which I regard as an even rarer thing to want to do if you are trying to handle non-nested property lists. Never-the-less I am not 100% happy in that I didn&apos;t try to test out what happens in such cases and perhaps the error handling will be less than ideal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14464673" author="paulk" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2008 18:58:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let me know if you are happy with the proposed fix and I will merge into 1.5.6 - code freeze is a few days away.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14464674" author="paulk" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2008 20:30:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added to 1.5.6 branch - let me know if there are any issues and we can back it out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
